[metadata]
Name:Fireball Divides X Evenly Among Two Targets
Goal:Win
Turns:5
Difficulty:Medium
Description:P0 casts Fireball (X R) with X=4 at two of the opponent's Hill Giants (3/3). Fireball deals "X damage divided evenly, rounded down, among any number of targets" (CR 601.2d): with X=4 over 2 targets each Hill Giant takes floor(4/2)=2 damage. The spell also costs {1} more for each target beyond the first (CR 601.2f), so casting at 2 targets costs X + R + {1}. With 6 Mountains the engine reserves mana for the per-target surcharge, chooses X=4, and both 3/3 Hill Giants survive with 2 damage marked (proving the damage was divided, not dealt in full to one target).

